name: 2016 Second Annual 5K Run/Walk
description:
Please join us in our efforts to raise awareness and research for Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome (EDS). Our hope is to be one step closer to finding a cure for this rare genetic connective tissue disorder.

REGISTER ONLINE TO SAVE $5 and RESERVE YOUR SPOT

$30 includes your registration fee and a James' Journey t-shirt

$15 includes your registration fee and no t-shirt -Children 10 and under are free

*RAIN OR SHINE!

-Runners start at 9:15AM -Walkers start at 9:30AM

Following the race will be a balloon release at 11:45AM in remembrance of James Kayler and all others lost to Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome.

*NO DOGS ALLOWED!

Proceeds will be donated to the James Kayler Fund through The University of Texas Health Science Center towards their research efforts in Vascular Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome.
